Scott County School District 1

  3d 
This is an update from SCSD1 concerning COVID-19 school protocols.
The CDC and Scott County Health Department are recommending the use of masks during the school day, but not requiring them.
SCSD1 will continue to follow our opening plan of requiring masks on all school buses with the use of masks still being optional during in-school activities.
We will continue to monitor the health situation in our school district and community and adjust policies for the health and safety of our students and staff as necessary.

While we are virtual, if you could continue to let the school know if your student tests positive for COVID. This helps us track student return dates. It also helps us manage future quarantines. Anyone that tests positive does not have to quarantine for 90 days from their positive test.
Thank you for your help.
Deana Broadus, RN BSN

Scott County School District 1

  1d 
Good morning everyone, due to the high rate of positive cases and the extremely high rate of student in quarantine, SCSD1 will be going to Virtual Learning starting Wednesday, August 11th. We hope to return to in person learning on Monday, August 23rd.
We will be providing grab and go lunch sites, please stay tuned for that information this evening.
As always, the health and safety of our students is our number one priority. We will continue to monitor the positivity rate
